article.headline: Hartford 62, Albany, N.Y. 42
article.story: HARTFORD, Conn. -- Milton Burton scored 17 points and Hartford routed Albany (N.Y.) 62-42 on Sunday. All eight of Burton's shots came from behind the 3-point arc, with five of them going in. He also made both of his free throws. The Hawks (5-10, 2-0 America East Conference) were 12 of 36 from 3-point range (33.3 percent) in their third straight win. Hartford, which shot 38.3 percent from the field (23 of 60), scored 22 points off of 17 Albany turnovers. The Hawks had nine steals and the Great Danes (8-10, 1-2) tallied just six assists and shot 34.8 percent from the floor (16 of 46). Genesis Maciel scored 12 points off the bench and Joe Zeglinski added 10 for Hartford, which had 13 players get at least three minutes of playing time. The Great Danes, who never led, were paced by Logan Aronhalt with 17 points. Mike Black added 10 points on 4 of 6 shooting for Albany.
